Index (XU100)  rose 0.8 percent to 59,854.80 at the midday break in
Istanbul. The gauge is up 8.6 percent this month, having
advanced in 14 of the past 15 days.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Polisan Holding AS (POLHO)  , a Turkish maker of paints
and dyes, rose to its highest since the shares began trading on
May 25, adding 0.9 percent to 2.23 liras, after saying its
chemicals unit started talks with foreign companies for a
production license for expandable polystyrene.  Turk Hava Yollari (THYAO)  AO, or Turkish Airlines,
headed for the highest in more than 10 months, adding 3.5
percent to 2.98 liras, after saying it will order at least 15
large aircraft as early as next month and is also looking at
about 10 acquisition prospects with no upper limit on
transaction size.  To contact the reporter on this story:
